literals: 'You are on a dirt road, it has come to an end and you can got left or right. Which way would you like to go? \n'
'You come to river, you can walk around it or swim across. Choose walk or swim. \n'
'You swim across and got eaten by an alligator'
'You walk for many miles, ran out of water and you lost the game.'
'You came to a bridge, it looks wobbly, do you want to cross it or head back? (cross/back) \n'
'You cross the bridge and meet a stranger, Do you talk to them? (yes/no) \n'
'You talk to the stranger and they gave you gold. You WINNN...!!!'
'You ignore the stranger and they shot you. You LOSE...!!!'
